Bug Report

Title: Mode desync between app UI and earbuds state after switching to Transparency Mode

Bug ID: B-01


Environment:
App version: (--)
Earbuds firmware: (--)
Device OS: iOS / Android (both observed)
Connection: Bluetooth (active)


Description:
When the user switches to Transparency Mode, the app immediately updates the UI to show Transparency Mode as active. 
However, the earbuds continue operating in Noise Cancellation Mode for 8–12 seconds. In some cases, after placing 
earbuds in the case and reconnecting, the app incorrectly still shows Transparency Mode while the earbuds are actually
in Noise Cancellation Mode.


Steps to Reproduce:
1.Connect earbuds to the app via Bluetooth.
2.Ensure earbuds are in Noise Cancellation Mode.
3.Select Transparency Mode in the app.
4.Observe app UI immediately after selection.
5.Wait 8–12 seconds and observe earbuds behavior.
6.Place earbuds in charging case and reconnect.
7.Check mode state in both app and earbuds.


Expected Result:
1.Earbuds should switch to Transparency Mode immediately or within 2 seconds.
2.App UI should reflect only the actual state of the earbuds.
3.After reconnection, both app and earbuds should show the same active mode.


Actual Result:
1.App immediately shows Transparency Mode as active.
2.Earbuds remain in Noise Cancellation Mode for 8–12 seconds.
3.After reconnect, app may still show Transparency Mode while earbuds are in Noise Cancellation Mode.


Impact:
1.UI and device state are inconsistent.
2.Users are misled about the actual active listening mode.
3.Potential safety and user experience concerns due to incorrect audio mode perception.


Severity: High
Priority: High
Type: Functional
